File: Police Minister Bheki Cele. JOHANNESBURG - Police Minister Bheki Cele is not ruling out extending the lockdown. Cele says the government's priority is ensuring people are safe. READ: COVID-19: SA on right track to mitigate job losses - expert "Remember we started with restriction, then we went to the lockdown. People are asking can we go beyond the lockdown and we are saying anything is possible", said Cele. Cele says the next step will be determined soon. "We would wish to go back to the normal life as soon as we can but we wish to go back there with the people alive." The number of South Africans to have died of COVID-19 now stands at 12. Confirmed cases have also risen to 1686. READ: COVID-19: Confirmed cases in SA continue to rise Gauteng has the most cases in South Africa with 713 confirmed infections. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.